{"name":"Magic Missile","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/magic_missile.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You fire two missiles of magical energy that strike enemies unerringly (the creatures must still be valid targets) and deal 1d4+1 force damage each. You can&rsquo;t target specific parts of a creature, and objects aren&rsquo;t damaged by this spell.</p>\n<p>You can target one or two enemies within 15 feet of one another, but each missile can strike only one creature. You must choose targets before you roll damage.</p>\n<p>If you give up your move on the turn you cast this, you can fire three missiles instead of two (at up to three enemies).</p>","level":1,"range":"100 feet","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"0UccgoLitXGpmGk0"}
{"name":"Daze","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/daze.png","data":{"class":"","type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You target an enemy with a CR of 2 or lower, causing it to lose its next turn! It can attempt a Will saving throw (DC = 10 + INT) to negate this effect. A creature dazed by this spell can&rsquo;t be affected by it again for 1 minute. This spell does not affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</p>","level":0,"range":"25 feet","duration":"1 round","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3G5LRf6MizPuRfxW"}},"_id":"1xhEhiM81Q7AUbDh"}
{"name":"Energy Ray","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/energy_ray.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You shoot a ray of acid, cold, electricity, or fire (choose each time you cast this) at an enemy or object. Make a ranged attack roll (page 79) against it. If you hit, the ray deals 1d4 damage of the chosen energy type.</p>","level":0,"range":"25 feet","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"22HcfX68A9OO2npy"}
{"name":"Inflict Pain","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/inflict_pain.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You telepathically rack an enemy with agonizing pain that imposes a &ndash;2 penalty on its ability checks, attack rolls, and skill checks. It can attempt a Will saving throw (DC = 12 + WIS). If it succeeds, the duration is only 1 round. This spell does not affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</p>","level":2,"range":"25 feet","duration":"1 round/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"2jH0LQ2IM05kpLsI"}
{"name":"Grease","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/grease.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You cover a 10-foot-square area with a layer of slippery grease. Any creature in the area when the spell is cast must succeed at a Reflex saving throw (DC = 11 + INT) or fall, losing its next move.</p>\n<p>A creature that tries to walk within or through the area of grease must first attempt an Athletics skill check (DC = 10). If a creature succeeds, it can move, though each square covered in grease takes an extra 5 feet (1 square) of movement. If a creature fails the check, it can&rsquo;t move. If a creature fails by 5 or more, it also falls, losing its next move.</p>","level":1,"range":"25 feet","duration":"1 minute/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"2q78RukEZ6FQM3q6"}
{"name":"Dancing Lights","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/dancing_light.png","data":{"class":"","type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You create up to four lights that resemble small headlights. The lights must stay within 10 feet of each other, but they can otherwise move 100 feet per round. A light winks out if the distance between you and it exceeds 100 feet. You can have only one dancing lights spell active at a time.</p>","level":0,"range":"100 feet","duration":"1 minute","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3G5LRf6MizPuRfxW"}},"_id":"7Bq80oYV162w1iMz"}
{"name":"Fear","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/fear.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>With a single mental nudge, you can unlock the deepest nightmares of a living creature of CR 4 or lower. It attempts a Will saving throw (DC = 11 + WIS). If it succeeds, it gains the hampered condition (page 86) for 1 round. If it fails, it gains the frightened condition (page 86). This spell does not affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</p>","level":1,"range":"25 feet","duration":"1d4 rounds","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"7NkhYwyrFi2QA76k"}
{"name":"Overheat","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/overheat.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You collect the heat generated by nearby bodies and devices and vent it outward in a 15-foot cone (page 83), dealing 2d8 fire damage to creatures and objects in the area. Each creature in the area can attempt a Reflex saving throw (DC = 11 + INT), taking only half damage (rounded down) if it succeeds.</p>","level":1,"range":"15 feet","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"7NqU7w8pPSNRHXEl"}
{"name":"Detect Magic","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/detect_magic.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You detect all magic spells, effects, items, and objects (including those on or affecting creatures) that you can see in range. When you cast this, you sense whether any are in range. One round later, you know how many there are. Another round later, you know exactly which things are magic. You can&rsquo;t detect magical traps in this way.</p>","level":0,"range":"60 feet","duration":"1 minute/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.x84S1XodIk81Z1uv"}},"_id":"9TYnHcnWV8y7zswr"}
{"name":"Psychokinetic Hand","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/psychokenetic_hand.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You can lift and move a small unattended object from a distance. Once per round, you can propel the object as far as 15 feet in any direction. The spell ends if the distance between you and the object exceeds 25 feet. You can&rsquo;t perform complex operations, such as firing a gun or using a computer, but you can shut a mechanical door or press a simple button.</p>","level":0,"range":"25 feet","duration":"1 round/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3hPVzFnPuWnH42ub"}},"_id":"9X7YltcHToqJZjV8"}
{"name":"Knock","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/knock.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You choose one physical or electronic lock within range and the spell tries to unlock it. Roll a d20 and add 14; if the result is equal to or exceeds the DC of the lock, then the lock opens and remains open.</p>","level":2,"range":"100 feet","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"BVwI7wDHXHZIob7G"}
{"name":"Telekinetic Projectile","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/t%C3%A9l%C3%A9kinetic_projectile.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You fling an object weighing up to 5 pounds at an enemy, making a ranged attack roll (page 79) against your target. If you hit, you deal 1d6 kinetic damage to the target.</p>","level":0,"range":"25 feet","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"CdGgRJaq2wIbxXzt"}
{"name":"Mind Thrust","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/mind_thrust.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You overload an enemy with a glut of psychic information, dealing 2d10 damage to it. The target can attempt a Will saving throw (DC = 11 + WIS) to take half damage (rounded down). This spell doesn&rsquo;t affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</p>","level":1,"range":"25 feet","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"Fe3kzaMa8ssW9QJy"}
{"name":"Levitate","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/charming_veneer.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>During this spell&rsquo;s duration, you can give up your normal move to move yourself or one willing or unconscious creature up or down (but not horizontally) up to 20 feet per round. A levitating creature that attacks with a melee or ranged weapon finds itself increasingly unstable; the first attack roll takes a &ndash;1 penalty, the second a &ndash;2 penalty, and so on, to a maximum of &ndash;5.</p>","level":2,"range":"25 feet","duration":"1 minute/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"FgS3F3txGREg3VX8"}
{"name":"Mystic Cure","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/mystic_cure.PNG","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsAllies","description":"<p>With a touch, you heal a living creature, restoring a number of Hit Points equal to 1d8 + WIS. If the target regains all of its Hit Points as a result of this healing, you can apply the remaining healing to yourself.</p>\n<p>On the other hand, if this isn&rsquo;t enough to restore all the target&rsquo;s Hit Points, you can transfer any number of your own Hit Points to the target, healing the target that amount. You can&rsquo;t transfer more Hit Points than you have or more Hit Points than the target is missing.</p>","level":1,"range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"GJctjcVanpSdMAUH"}
{"name":"Telepathic Message","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/telepathic_message.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You can send a short telepathic message to up to one creature per character level you have. Creatures that receive the message can reply telepathically, but you can send at most one message each round, and each message can&rsquo;t exceed 10 words. This spell does not affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</p>","level":0,"range":"100 feet","duration":"10 minutes/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.AjLWk1LAqDmMMEuE"}},"_id":"GsToiSo7W9dZ6jxL"}
{"name":"Caustic Conversion","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/caustic_conversion.jpg","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">You fling magical nanites that convert water vapor around your </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">target into deadly acid. Make a ranged attack roll (page 79) </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">against one enemy or object. If you hit, the target takes 4d4 </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">acid damage, and it takes 5 additional acid damage at the end of </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">its turn each round for the spell&rsquo;s duration.</span></p>","level":2,"range":"100 feet","duration":"2 rounds","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"H21Z5jEBm06JdOcI"}
{"name":"Token Spell","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/token_spell.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>Once cast, token spell enables you to perform simple magical effects for 1 hour. The effects are minor. You can slowly lift an unattended object weighing 1 pound or less. You can alter items in a 1-foot cube each round, coloring, cleaning, soiling, cooling, warming, or flavoring them. You can create small objects, but they look artificial and are extremely fragile (they can&rsquo;t be used as tools or weapons). Any actual change to an object (beyond moving, cleaning, or soiling it) persists for only 1 hour.</p>","level":0,"range":"10 feet","duration":"1 hour","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ylO6IuCzS8ME0qhW"}},"_id":"I67PlFK5kyjG7r7q"}
{"name":"Fatigue","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/fatigue.PNG","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>Make a melee attack roll (page 78) against an adjacent enemy (including diagonally), with a +2 bonus to your attack roll. If you hit, the target attempts a Fortitude saving throw (DC = 10 + WIS). If it fails, the target gains the hampered condition (page 86) for the spell&rsquo;s duration.</p>","level":0,"range":"Touch","duration":"1 round/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.nGPz1in6OPPcLTSX"}},"_id":"JmOuL3nsvUVv6Qog"}
{"name":"Daze Monster","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/daze_monster.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">You target an enemy with a CR of 5 or lower, causing it to lose its next turn! It can attempt a Will saving throw (DC = 12 + WIS) to negate this effect. A creature dazed by this spell can&rsquo;t be affected by it again for 1 minute. This spell does not affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</span></p>","level":2,"range":"100 feet","duration":"1 round","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"LESi3CaWhoOnrVM1"}
{"name":"Keen Senses","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/keen_senses.PNG","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You or an ally gains a +2 bonus to Perception skill checks.</p>","level":1,"range":"Touch","duration":"1 minute/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"LuNwJz5uNeeMjf7e"}
{"name":"Detect Thoughts","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/detect_thoughts.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You detect the surface thoughts of creatures around you. For the duration of the spell, you can forgo taking other actions to gain more and more information.</p>\n<p>When you cast this spell, you detect the presence or absence of thoughts from conscious creatures in range. One round later, you detect the number of thinking minds. The next round, and each round thereafter, you can read the surface thoughts of a target mind in the area.</p>\n<p>A target can attempt a Will saving throw (DC = 11 + WIS) to negate this effect. This spell does not affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</p>","level":1,"range":"60 feet","duration":"1 minute/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"MUPuAFoCPvX7RsEu"}
{"name":"Holographic Image","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/ghost_sound.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You weave nearby photons into an illusory holographic image that can take almost any form you can imagine. These holograms are usually effective against cameras, robots, and living creatures. The image can include minor sounds, but not understandable speech. The image has no smell, texture, or temperature, and it can&rsquo;t extend beyond four 10-foot cubes. You can move the image within the limits of the size of the effect.</p>\n<p>Each time you cast this, you can take the Use a Special Ability action on subsequent turns to maintain the hologram; this doesn&rsquo;t use more spell slots. The hologram persists for 2 rounds (12 seconds) after you stop taking the Use a Special Ability action to maintain it.</p>","level":2,"range":"400 feet","duration":"2 rounds","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"Mf0FCthozwQyksdd"}
{"name":"Charm Person","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/charm_person.jpg","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You make a creature regard you as a trusted ally. It can attempt a Will saving throw (DC = 11 + WIS) to negate this effect. If you or your allies have attacked the creature in the past minute, it gets a +5 bonus to its saving throw.</p>\n<p>You can&rsquo;t directly control a charmed creature, but you can give it suggestions. A charmed creature ignores obviously harmful suggestions. Any act by you or your allies that threatens the charmed creature breaks the spell. This spell does not affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</p>","level":1,"range":"25 feet","duration":"1 hour/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"NiJI0QyX3NcoIEc7"}
{"name":"Force Blast","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/force_blast.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">You gather mystical energy and blast it outward in a 30-foot cone </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">(page 83). Creatures in the area take 2d6 damage and are pushed </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">back 5 feet. Each creature can attempt a Reflex saving throw </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">(DC = 12 + WIS). A creature that succeeds takes half damage </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">(rounded down) and is not pushed back.</span></p>","level":2,"range":"30 feet","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"O3N8XZOtNdXKLF6i"}
{"name":"See Invisibility","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/see_invisibility.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>Invisible objects and creatures (such as those affected by the invisibility spell) become visible to you as translucent shapes. This doesn&rsquo;t enable you to see creatures that are simply hiding using Stealth, are behind a wall, or are otherwise hard to see.</p>","level":2,"range":"Personal","duration":"10 minutes/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"Pj3Esz14MeaYaTt1"}
{"name":"Spider Climb","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/spider_climb.PNG","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You or an ally can climb on vertical surfaces or even traverse ceilings as efficiently as a spider does. The affected creature doesn&rsquo;t need to attempt Athletics skill checks to climb (page 47) to traverse a vertical or horizontal surface (even upside down), and it doesn&rsquo;t gain the flat-footed condition from climbing.</p>","level":2,"range":"Touch","duration":"10 minutes/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"UvZSohWWaQLOAT8J"}
{"name":"Greater Mystic Cure","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/mystic_cure.PNG","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsAllies","description":"<p>With a touch, you heal a living creature, restoring a number of Hit Points equal to 3d8 + WIS. If the target regains all of its Hit Points as a result of this healing, you can apply the remaining healing to yourself.</p>\n<p>On the other hand, if this isn&rsquo;t enough to restore all the target&rsquo;s Hit Points, you can transfer any number of your own Hit Points to the target, healing the target that amount. You can&rsquo;t transfer more Hit Points than you have or more Hit Points than the target is missing.</p>","level":2,"range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"ZHOO8Myp9DwOsNkX"}
{"name":"Detect Radiation","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/detect_radiation.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You detect any radiation in range. The spell can penetrate barriers, but 3 feet of dirt or wood, 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or any force field blocks it.</p>","level":1,"range":"120 feet","duration":"10 minutes/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"aGnqym7YIpKQ3L5D"}
{"name":"Slow Fall","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/slow.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsAllies","description":"<p>You target one falling object or creature per level. All targets must be within 20 feet of each other. The affected targets instantly fall slower, taking no damage upon landing. You can cast this when it&rsquo;s not your turn (so you can cast it as soon as a creature falls, before they hit the ground), but if you do, you lose your action on your next turn.</p>","level":1,"range":"25 feet","duration":"1 round/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"bjb7SYEnR8GsCzLi"}
{"name":"Jolting Surge","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/jolting_surge.PNG","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You touch an enemy or object with an object you&rsquo;re holding that uses electricity. Make a melee attack roll (page 78) against the target. If you hit, your electrical device surges out of control, dealing 4d6 electricity damage to your target.</p>\n<p>Alternatively, you can touch an electrical device your target is wearing (or a target that is itself an electrical device, such as a robot) directly, gaining a +2 bonus to your attack roll.</p>","level":1,"range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"eG9w89f4FYk3R7nY"}
{"name":"Microbot Assault","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/microbot_assault.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You form a cloud of fist-sized flying microbots that fills a 10-foot-square area and can share squares with other creatures. Any enemy in the same square as the microbots takes a &ndash;2 penalty to its Armor Class and attack rolls.</p>\n<p>Each time you cast&nbsp;this, you can take the Use a Special Ability action on subsequent&nbsp;turns to maintain the cloud; this doesn&rsquo;t use more spell slots.</p>\n<p>After you cast this spell, and after you take the Use a Special ability action to maintain the cloud, the microbots pursue the nearest enemy, using their 20-foot flying speed.</p>","level":2,"range":"25 feet","duration":"1 round","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"g6jOPYdg67qGq5Bv"}
{"name":"Reflecting Armor","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/reflecting_armor.PNG","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>During this spell&rsquo;s duration, when you take damage from an enemy&rsquo;s melee or ranged attack, you can end this spell. If you do, energy arcs through the air to strike the attacking creature, which takes an amount of damage equal to the damage dealt to you at the time this spell was dismissed (maximum 10).</p>\n<p>The target can attempt a Reflex saving throw (DC = 11 + WIS) to take half damage (rounded down). The damage type is the same as that of the initial attack.</p>","level":1,"range":"Personal","duration":"10 minutes/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"gzxUrLM2RfzYtIWc"}
{"name":"Greater Fear","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/fear.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>With a single mental nudge, you can unlock the deepest nightmares of a living creature of CR 4 or lower. It attempts a Will saving throw (DC = 12 + WIS). If it succeeds, it gains the hampered condition (page 86) for 1 round. If it fails, it gains the frightened condition (page 86). This spell does not affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</p>","level":2,"range":"100 feet","duration":"1 minute","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"jGp43tXClSBkO91A"}
{"name":"Invisibility","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/invilibility.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsAllies","description":"<p>You make an ally (and the ally&rsquo;s equipment) invisible. An invisible creature can&rsquo;t be attacked or targeted with a spell unless the attacker has a way to see invisible things (such as the see invisibility spell below). The invisibility spell ends early if the invisible creature attacks or casts a harmful spell.</p>","level":2,"range":"Touch","duration":"1 minute/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"jeiRRDp1IECHYUzY"}
{"name":"Hold Portal","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/hold_portal.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You magically hold shut a door, gate, shutter, or window made of any standard material (metal, plastic, stone, wood, and so on) as if it were securely closed and locked.</p>\n<p>A knock spell (page 45) can negate a hold portal spell.</p>\n<p>Add 5 to the normal DC for breaking through a door (Game Master&rsquo;s Guide 46) or hacking an electronic lock (Game Master&rsquo;s Guide 47) affected by this spell.</p>","level":1,"range":"100 feet","duration":"1 minute/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"oA1K3C3IxcnW91ON"}
{"name":"Ghost Sound","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/hologram_memory.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You create a volume of sound as noisy as 20 normal humans. Thus, you can create shouting, singing, talking, or marching sounds, as well as sounds of battle or small explosions. You can make noises that sound like machines or the roar of an alien predator, but you can&rsquo;t make specific sounds such as intelligible speech or the exact hum of a particular starship&rsquo;s engines.</p>","level":0,"range":"25 feet","duration":"1 round/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SX7YTrt2Hcn5To7r"}},"_id":"ok9rrvpOJmICORFF"}
{"name":"Greater Mind Thrust","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/mind_thrust.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You overload an enemy with a glut of psychic information, dealing 4d10 damage to it. The target can attempt a Will saving throw (DC = 12 + WIS) to take half damage (rounded down). This spell doesn&rsquo;t affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</p>","level":2,"range":"25 feet","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"pM50u5cA7CSWs7rm"}
{"name":"Command","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/command.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You give a living creature one of the following commands, which it obeys to the best of its ability on its next turn. It can attempt a Will saving throw (DC = 11 + WIS) to negate this effect. This spell does not affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</p>\n<p><strong>Approach:</strong> The target moves toward you as quickly and directly as possible for 1 round, taking no other actions.</p>\n<p><strong>Drop:</strong> The target drops whatever it is holding. It can&rsquo;t pick up any dropped item until its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Flee:</strong> The target moves away from you as quickly and directly as possible for 1 round, taking no other actions.</p>\n<p><strong>Stop:</strong> The target loses its next move. It can otherwise act normally.</p>","level":1,"range":"25 feet","duration":"1 round","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"qKayWALr7kT2UDsD"}
{"name":"Supercharge Weapon","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/supercharge_weapon.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You supercharge a weapon. If the weapon&rsquo;s next attack hits (provided it is made before the end of the next round), the attack deals 4d6 additional damage, though if the weapon deals damage to multiple creatures, it deals 2d6 additional damage instead. This bonus damage is of the same type as the weapon&rsquo;s normal damage.</p>","level":1,"range":"Touch","duration":"1 round","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"qjECyAf35KT7FpVJ"}
{"name":"Remove Condition","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/remove_condition_lesser.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsAllies","description":"<p>You remove one of the following conditions from yourself or an ally: frightened, hampered, impaired, or staggered.</p>","level":2,"range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"tLoodproKObf2wda"}
{"name":"Mirror Image","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/mirror_image.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You create 1d4 holographic doubles of yourself that inhabit your square, making it more difficult for enemies to hit you. These images move with you, mimicking your movements, sounds, and actions exactly.</p>\n<p>When an enemy would hit you with an attack (or with a spell that uses an attack roll), roll a d20. If the die shows 1&ndash;10, you are hit as normal. If the die shows 11&ndash;20, one of your holographic doubles is destroyed instead.</p>","level":2,"range":"Personal","duration":"1 minute/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"ttOtBzhQnyizFcwc"}
{"name":"Inject Nanobots","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/inject_nanobot.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You create tiny nanobots and inject them into a living or robotic enemy. Make a melee attack roll (page 78) against the target. If you hit, the target takes 4d8 damage and gains the staggered condition (page 87) for a number of rounds equal to your character level.</p>\n<p>The target can attempt a Fortitude saving throw (DC = 12 + INT); if it succeeds, it takes only half damage (rounded down) and doesn&rsquo;t gain the staggered condition.</p>","level":2,"range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"uKXJmV5LLrOU7z8x"}
{"name":"Hold Person","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/hold_person.jpg","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsEnemies","description":"<p>You freeze a creature in place. It is aware and breathes normally, but it can&rsquo;t move, take any actions, or even talk. It can attempt a Will save (DC = 12 + WIS) to negate this spell when you cast it, and while affected by the spell, at the end of each of its turns it can attempt a new saving throw to end it. This spell does not affect creatures with the unliving defensive ability.</p>","level":2,"range":"100 feet","duration":"1 round/character level","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"xZ85S6GqmeY3HIY7"}
{"name":"Lesser Remove Condition","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/remove_condition.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"targetsAllies","description":"<p>You remove either the hampered condition or the staggered condition from yourself or an ally.</p>","level":1,"range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"ydNZEc0njTLdXg1F"}
{"name":"Minor Holographic Image","type":"spell","img":"systems/sfrpgbb/icons/spells/holographic_image.png","data":{"class":null,"type":"utilitySpell","description":"<p>You weave nearby photons into an illusory holographic image that can take almost any form you can imagine. These holograms are usually effective against cameras, robots, and living creatures. The image has no sound, smell, texture, or temperature, and it can&rsquo;t extend beyond four 10-foot cubes. You can move the image within the limits of the size of the effect.</p>\n<p>Each time you cast this, you can take the Use a Special Ability action on subsequent turns to maintain the hologram; this doesn&rsquo;t use more spell slots.</p>","level":1,"range":"400 feet","duration":"1 round","save":{"hasSave":true,"baseDC":10,"bonusAbility":null,"savetype":"reflex"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"H1Kqxhmh5dh6djUL":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z6bQByvdISQFgxC8"}},"_id":"z4SrHyxy2FIkzNtc"}
